Comment: The experiment was carried out at a Van de Graaff accelerator and the target was a thin film of GdF3 evaporated onto a thin film of Al. 
	  The listed uncertainties in the cross-section values are statistical and also due to peak area determination. 
	  There is a systematic uncertainty of 10% (see Sigma scale factor fields). 
	  As the gamma-ray line is isotropic the cross section values correspond to total cross section.			
			
